The paper deals with an extension of answer set programming (ASP), which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces a possibilistic logic characterization of answer sets, which falls under the category of mathematical logic (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper provides a syntactic counterpart and implementation details, which are related to programming languages and compilers (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE), respectively. Finally, the paper deals with constraints and distributions, which are related to data structures (cs.DS).
